page.title: 06ECOLOGY.
page.content:
Ernocroft Wood:
The large wood which is part of the Etherow Country Park is mainly deciduous trees, which we marked on the map as item 14. When I say deciduous trees I mean they lose their leaves in Winter. The wood is very big and probably contains lots of wildlife. We thought this because we saw some rabbits run into the wood. We saw most of the wood from the Glossop Road and also from the road leading to Cote Green. I also noticed a small cluster of conifers in the wood. These conifers were at the far side of the wood. I saw that some of the trees didn't have any leaves yet but I don't know why.
